laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast
laboratory_examinations.findings: Appendix is enlarged, hyperemic with wall thickening, measuring up to 13 mm. Moderate fat stranding in the right lower quadrant, mild thickening of adjacent terminal ileum and cecum, small amount of nonhemorrhagic ascites noted.
Liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout, with no evidence of focal lesions, and no biliary dilatation.
Kidneys are of normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram, no evidence of focal renal lesions or hydronephrosis.
